				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">After every sprite is written to the oam buffer, there is a routine that changes every pair of coordinates from 16-bit to 8-bit that also deals with offscreen sprites.</div><br />I see... That's the type of thing that could make the whole process slower though, since you have to run through the data one more time.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I chose ADDing just in case the same sprite patterns are located at a different spot of v-ram depending on the level.</div>
<br />Ah OK. I only EOR the attribute byte (flipping, palette, priority), the pattern index can be added to something in my case too. The coordinates can't be overridden though (I don't see the point).</div>

